Despite the preference for exposing the (111) facets at the pillar growth front, the metal lattice of the pillars is growing approximately in the [001] direction, as can be seen in an x-ray diffraction Ir (111) pole figure in Figure 7b. Four slightly elongated diffraction peaks appear at 45° positions relative to the [100] and [010] in-plane directions of the SrTiO3 host lattice. This shows that the Ir metal does indeed grow in the 100Ir||100SrTiO3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
